Introduction

Asaya Jurin, known under her stage name Jurin, is a Japanese rapper, dancer, singer, model, choreographer, and snowboarder under XGALX. She is best known as the leader, main dancer, and lead rapper of the Japanese global girl group XG.

Jurin started snowboarding at a young age and her goal was to become a pro athlete, and she achieved it at 12 the age 12 so she decided to be in a girl group and express it which led her to debut in XG. She has been a fashion model for Droptokyo, Popteen, and more since she was 15.

On January 29, 2022, Jurin was revealed as the first member of XG. The group officially debuted on Mar 18, 2022, with their debut digital single "Tippy Toes".
